                  THE "DO WHATEVER, HONESTLY" LICENSE
                           (v1, no take-backs)

This is open source the way a potluck is open. Show up, grab a plate, bring
something back if you feel like it. No copyright. No lawyers. None of that
"all rights reserved" energy.

The whole deal:

  Take this skill and go nuts. Fork it, ship it, sell it, rename it, teach a
  robot with it, paste it into your game, print it out and tape it to your
  wall. You don't have to ask. You don't have to credit anybody, though a nod
  is nice, like waving at a neighbor. Nothing to pay. Nobody to email.

  This work is dedicated to the public domain. Whoever wrote it gives up every
  copyright claim, anywhere, forever. It belongs to everyone now. Which is just
  a roundabout way of saying it belongs to no one, and that's the point.

  Live somewhere that doesn't believe in the public domain? Fine. Then consider
  this a license to do absolutely anything the law lets you, free of charge,
  for as long as copyright would have lasted.

And the boring part, because it has to be here:

  THE SKILL IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITH NO WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. If it breaks your
  game, eats your DataStore, or somehow summons a moderator, that is a you
  problem. Nobody is getting sued. Not the author, not the contributors, not
  you. Back up your work and actually read the code before you trust it with
  anything that matters.

That's it. Go build something cool.
